{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/conceit/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Developer's blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"ed784ad0-400b-5115-91cb-8a5db3c4b079","excerpt":"Meaning Conceit is a noun with two main meanings: Excessive pride in oneself — an attitude of vanity or arrogance. A fanciful or extended metaphor used in…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#meaning\">Meaning</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\">Grammar and Usage</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#sentence-structures\">Sentence structures:</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#common-phrases\">Common Phrases</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#collocations\">Collocations</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#examples\">Examples</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\">Synonyms or Related</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#antonym\">Antonym</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","html":"<h2 id=\"meaning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#meaning\" aria-label=\"meaning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Meaning</h2>\n<p><strong>Conceit</strong> is a noun with two main meanings:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Excessive pride in oneself</strong> — an attitude of vanity or arrogance.</li>\n<li><strong>A fanciful or extended metaphor</strong> used in literature or poetry.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"grammar-and-usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\" aria-label=\"grammar and usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Grammar and Usage</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Part of speech:</strong> noun</li>\n<li>Usually uncountable when referring to pride (e.g., <em>full of conceit</em>).</li>\n<li>Can be countable when referring to a literary device (e.g., <em>a clever conceit in the poem</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"sentence-structures\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sentence-structures\" aria-label=\"sentence structures permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sentence structures:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\"be full of conceit\"</li>\n<li>\"display/express conceit\"</li>\n<li>\"conceit of comparing A to B\" (literary use)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-phrases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-phrases\" aria-label=\"common phrases permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common Phrases</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Full of conceit</li>\n<li>Intellectual conceit</li>\n<li>A clever conceit (literary)</li>\n<li>A poetic conceit</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collocations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collocations\" aria-label=\"collocations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collocations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Adjective + conceit:</strong> sheer conceit, intellectual conceit, poetic conceit</li>\n<li><strong>Verb + conceit:</strong> display conceit, reveal conceit, disguise conceit</li>\n<li><strong>Preposition + conceit:</strong> out of conceit, with conceit</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>His constant bragging showed how full of <strong>conceit</strong> he was.</li>\n<li>She entered the room with such <strong>conceit</strong> that no one wanted to talk to her.</li>\n<li>The poet’s clever <strong>conceit</strong> compared life to a fragile glass vase.</li>\n<li>Intellectual <strong>conceit</strong> can prevent people from admitting their mistakes.</li>\n<li>He disguised his <strong>conceit</strong> under false modesty.</li>\n<li>The novel is structured around the <strong>conceit</strong> of a journey through time.</li>\n<li>Her success gave her a sense of <strong>conceit</strong> that annoyed her colleagues.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"synonyms-or-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\" aria-label=\"synonyms or related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Synonyms or Related</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>For pride:</strong> arrogance, vanity, egotism, hubris</li>\n<li><strong>For literary sense:</strong> metaphor, simile, figure of speech</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"antonym\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#antonym\" aria-label=\"antonym permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Antonym</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>For pride:</strong> humility, modesty</li>\n<li><strong>For literary sense:</strong> plain statement, literal expression</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"conceit meaning and examples","date":"2025-09-07","description":"English learning materials; conceit explanation.","tags":["English","noun","adjective"],"featuredImage":{"publicURL":"/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/conceit.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8e898","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/b5658/conceit.png","srcSet":"/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/acb7c/conceit.png 256w,\n/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/ccc41/conceit.png 512w,\n/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/b5658/conceit.png 1024w","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/22bfc/conceit.webp 256w,\n/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/d689f/conceit.webp 512w,\n/static/e99e5d16ab39dee44e0d2a4d5bdfbe65/67ded/conceit.webp 1024w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"}]},"width":1024,"height":1024}}}}},"relatedPosts":{"nodes":[]},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/authentic/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"authentic meaning and examples"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/consequent/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"consequent meaning and examples"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"ed784ad0-400b-5115-91cb-8a5db3c4b079","previousPostId":"a8f16d7c-4ac5-55a9-b32b-bfeb9b4b719a","nextPostId":"301b0697-7af8-514c-9d6a-d754d6a75a44","relatedPosts":[]}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"],"slicesMap":{}}